<head>
<title>Llewellyn H. Rockwell, Jr.</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/paper2.jpg">
<center>
<h2>Llewellyn H. Rockwell, Jr.</h2>
</center> 
 <br>
<hr>
<br>
Llewellyn H. Rockwell, Jr., is founder and president of the Ludwig von Mises Institute, a non-profit, educational organization in Auburn, Ala. 36849.
<p>
The Mises Institute, founded in 1982 and named for the great economist, is dedicated to free markets, sound money, private property, and less government. It sponsors student scholarships, teaching programs, books, and the monthly <i>Free Market,</i> and is the center of the resurgent Austrian School of economics.
<p>
A former Congressional aide, magazine editor, and college administrator, Lew Rockwell writes for the <i>Washington Times,</i> the <i>Birmingham News,</i> the <i>Los Angeles Times,</i> and other newspapers. He is the editor of five books, and of the <i>Rothbard-Rockwell Report,</i> published by the Center for Libertarian Studies in Burlingame, Cal.
<p>

<br> 

</body>
