<body>
<h3>Important!</h3>
You <b>must</b> enter your e-mail address in the correct form for <b>use on the
Internet</b>. The address you enter is used to e-mail your subscriptions. So
it must be correct!
<p>
The correct form for an internet e-mail address is <i>user@host</i> where
<i>user</i> is the your local e-mail account, and <i>host</i> is the internet
address for your host. For example:
<p>
<dl>
<dt><b>example@frc.org</b>
<dd>is a valid e-mail address
<dt>example
<dd>is not.
</dl>
<p>
If you are a <b>Compuserve</b> user, and your Compuserve id is <b>103,93</b>,
your <b>Internet</b> e-mail address is
<dl>
<dt><b>103.93@compuserve.com</b>
<dd>Note that the &quot;,&quot; has been replaced with &quot;.&quot;. Entering
<dt>103,9
<dd>will not work!
</dl>
<p>
If you are an <b>AOL</b> user, and your AOL account is MyName,
your <b>Internet</b> e-mail address is
<dl>
<dt><b>MyName@aol.com</b>
<dd>Entering
<dt>MyName
<dd>will not work!
</dl>
If you are a <b>Prodigy</b> user, and your account is ESXN34J,
your <b>Internet</b> e-mail address is
<dl>
<dt><b>ESXN34J@prodigy.com</b>
<dd>Entering
<dt>ESXN34J
<dd>will not work!
</dl>
<p>You must enter just one e-mail address.
<p>If you want to test out your e-mail address before submitting the subscription 
form, enter what you think is your e-mail address in the box:<p>
<form action="/townhall/test-email.perl.cgi" method="post">
<input type="text" size="40" name="address">
<p>Then press the 
<p><input type="submit" value="Submit">
</form>
<p>button. If it is correct, you should receive an e-mail shortly afterwards confirming 
that it is your correct e-mail address.
<p>
<a href="/townhall/FRC/subscribe/subscribe-u.html">Return</a> to the 
subscription screen.
</body>
</html>
