<TITLE>Douglas Seay -- Heritage </TITLE>

<H3>
DOUGLAS SEAY</H3>
<HR>
<B>Director, The Project on Federalism and the States</B>
<P><IMG SRC="/heritage/staff/pics/seay.jpe" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10>
<P>
Seay manages Heritage's Project on Federalism and the States, which encourages the nation's governors to become more directly involved in Washington policy-making as it affects the states. Seay, Heritage's former Deputy Director of  Foreign and Defense Policy Studies, previously held a fellowship at Harvard University's Center for Science and International Affairs. Seay is a graduate of Georgetown University's School of Foreign Service and a former Foreign Service Officer.

