    <p><li>Michael Novak, <I>The New Consensus on Family and Welfare</I> (Washington, D.C.: American Enterprise Institute, 1987), p. 34.
    <p><li> Heritage Foundation research based on the National Longitudinal Survey of Youth.
   <p><li> James S. Coleman, "Social Capital in the Creation of Human Capital," <I>American Journal of Sociology,</I> Vol. 94, Supplement (1988), p. S1115.
    <p><li> Heritage Foundation research based on the National Longitudinal Survey of Youth.
    <p><li> See Denis Doyle, "The Social Consequences of Choice: Why It Matters Where Poor Children Go to School," Heritage Foundation <I>Backgrounder</I> No. 1088, July 25, 1996.
